      <acqinfo id="aspace_c4e036f439555b85b790c498742179e7">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Yale Bookplate Collection was formerly housed in Sterling Memorial Library. The collection was incorporated into the Arts of the Book Collection in 1984 and then moved to the Seeley G. Mudd Library in 1990. In 2011 it was transferred to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_98eaf662d97be841505ef16bbe2a9d9d">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_eb2a9fcf315d7a97e31ef21aba1297d5">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_f665518920a1bbc88cadb92cec9bce44">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates by Jan Battermann, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0c612cc71da5fa2ca7b99045a86334fc">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Johannes "Jan" Battermann (1909-1999) was a Dutch graphic artist and painter active in Amsterdam.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ab8b654c81ea7773e7a15bd054d4e71a">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains bookplates by Jan Battermann, a Dutch graphic artist and painter. In addition to ex-libris designs, the collection also contains a few examples of Battermann's other graphic works, including New Year's cards.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_16a291b75328eb200501ed12857359af">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Bookplates. II. Other Works. III. Ephemera.</p>  
      </arrangement>
